This paper is primarily focused on networking and communication in vehicular networks, which falls under the category of "Computer Science - Networking and Internet Architecture" (cs.NI). The use of coalition formation games suggests a game-theoretic approach, which could also place this paper in the "Computer Science - Game Theory" (cs.GT) category. Information theory (cs.IT) may also be relevant, as the paper discusses the transmission and reception of data over wireless channels. Additionally, the paper addresses security concerns related to content distribution, which could place it in the "Computer Science - Cryptography and Security" (cs.CR) category. Finally, the use of cooperative approaches and broadcasting strategies could also relate to the "Computer Science - Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing" (cs.DC) category.
